#: /home/gareth/splunk/etc/apps/windows/appserver/static/perfmgmt.html:2
#, python-format
msgid ""
"Splunk can query multiple hosts for performance information, and allow "
"you to search that data, chart it and alert on it. Here are our favorites"
" below. Don't like our dashboard? Build your own; the <strong><a "
"href=\"%(url)s\">Getting Started</a></strong> app can show you how."
msgstr ""

#: /home/gareth/splunk/etc/apps/windows/appserver/static/perfmgmt.html:5
msgid "What am I looking at?"
msgstr ""

#: /home/gareth/splunk/etc/apps/windows/appserver/static/perfmgmt.html:7
msgid ""
"Below is a performance chart similar to the default view in perfmon, "
"looking over the last day."
msgstr ""

#: /home/gareth/splunk/etc/apps/windows/appserver/static/perfmgmt.html:8
msgid ""
"Each of the four smaller boxes is a search borrowed from the "
"<strong>Performance Management</strong> menu above. You can drill down "
"into any of four areas."
msgstr ""

#: /home/gareth/splunk/etc/apps/windows/appserver/static/perfmgmt.html:12
#, python-format
msgid ""
"Note that these searches depend on indexing WMI data. If that's not "
"enabled in the <strong><a href=\"%(wmiurl)s\">WMI inputs</a></strong> "
"section of <strong><a href=\"%(mgrurl)s\">Manager</a></strong>, you won't"
" see anything below."
msgstr ""

#: /home/gareth/splunk/etc/apps/windows/appserver/static/perfmgmt.html:16
#, python-format
msgid ""
"If you see gaps in your trend lines, it's probably because your system was"
" off, or Splunk couldn't connect to the other machines you asked it to. "
"Here is more information on <strong><a href=\"%(url)s\">diagnosing WMI "
"connectivity errors</a></strong>."
msgstr ""

#: /home/gareth/splunk/etc/apps/windows/appserver/static/systemmgmt-zh_TW.html:11
